#%Module1.0

module-whatis       "VirtualGL is an open source toolkit that gives any Linux or Unix remote display software the ability to run OpenGL applications with full hardware acceleration"
module-url          "https://github.com/VirtualGL/virtualgl"
module-license      "wxWindows Library Licence, Version 3.1"
module-maintainer   "Jo√£o Pedro Agostinho de Sousa <joao.agostinho-de-sousa@psi.ch>"
module-help "
VirtualGL is an open-source software package that allows hardware-accelerated
3D rendering for remote display environments like VNC or X11 forwarding. It
works by redirecting an application's 3D rendering commands from a client
machine to a powerful server with a 3D accelerator. The server performs the
rendering, and VirtualGL streams the resulting images back to the client for
display, enabling high-performance 3D applications on less-powerful or thin
clients.
"
